Constructs a tiledb_filter object

Source: R/Filter.R
tiledb_filter.Rd

Available filters:

  • "NONE"

  • "GZIP"

  • "ZSTD"

  • "LZ4"

  • "RLE"

  • "BZIP2"

  • "DOUBLE_DELTA"

  • "BIT_WIDTH_REDUCTION"

  • "BITSHUFFLE"

  • "BYTESHUFFLE"

  • "POSITIVE_DELTA"

tiledb_filter(name = "NONE", ctx = tiledb:::ctx)

Arguments

name

(default "NONE") TileDB filter name string
ctx

tiledb_ctx object

Value

tiledb_filter object

Details

Valid compression options vary depending on the filter used, consult the TileDB docs for more information.

Examples

tiledb_filter("ZSTD")
#> An object of class "tiledb_filter"
#> Slot "ptr":
#> <pointer: 0x55b2dd8ac350>
#>
